African Dawn, Gold Reef, Metorex, PSG Group: South African Equity Preview

-- B y   S i k o n a t h i   M a n t s h a n t s h a
-- 
2011-06-14T22:00:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-14/gold-reef-metorex-psg-group-south-african-equities-preview.html
The following stocks may rise or
fall in  South Africa . Symbols are in parentheses and prices are
from the last close.  The FTSE/JSE Africa All Share Index advanced for a second
day, adding 52.78, or 0.2 percent, to 31,229.36 at the 5 p.m.
close in Johannesburg.  African Dawn Capital Ltd. (ADW)  : The small-cap financial
services company plans to raise about 36.7 million rand ($5.4
million) by issuing new shares at 10 cents per share, the
company said in a regulatory filing. Shareholders owning more
than 40 percent of the stock have already agreed to the issue.
The stock was unchanged at 9 cents.  Gold Reef Resorts Ltd. (GDF)  : The South African hotel
and gaming company holds an annual  shareholders’ meeting . Gold
Reef increased 50 cents, or 3.1 percent, to 16.50 rand.  Metorex Ltd. (MTX)  : The producer of copper holds a
shareholders’ meeting. The stock rose 2 cents, or 0.3 percent,
to 7.30 rand.  PSG Group Ltd. (PSG)  : The investment holding group holds
a shareholders’ meeting. The stock declined 98 cents, or 2
percent, to 47.92 rand.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Sikonathi Mantshantsha in Johannesburg at 
 smantshantsh@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
